<item>
            <title>[FELIX-3150] Filter parameter is ignored at getServiceReferences</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/FELIX-3150</link>
                <project id="12310100" key="FELIX">Felix</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;The method&lt;br/&gt;
public &amp;lt;S&amp;gt; Collection&amp;lt;ServiceReference&amp;lt;S&amp;gt;&amp;gt; BundleContext::getServiceReferences(Class&amp;lt;S&amp;gt; clazz, String filter)&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;is ignoring the filter parameter. Looking at BundleContextImpl code, it looks like that is the case&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;   public &amp;lt;S&amp;gt; Collection&amp;lt;ServiceReference&amp;lt;S&amp;gt;&amp;gt; getServiceReferences(&lt;br/&gt;
       Class&amp;lt;S&amp;gt; clazz, String filter)&lt;br/&gt;
       throws InvalidSyntaxException&lt;/p&gt;
   {
       ServiceReference&amp;lt;S&amp;gt;[] refs =
           (ServiceReference&amp;lt;S&amp;gt;[]) getServiceReferences(clazz.getName(), null);   /// The filter param should be here instead of the null.
       return (refs == null)
           ? Collections.EMPTY_LIST
           : (Collection&amp;lt;ServiceReference&amp;lt;S&amp;gt;&amp;gt;) Arrays.asList(refs);
   }
</description>
